snippet.textDisplay:
Geez, I'm glad they made this video. Other than liking D&D, this video made me aware that YT apparently unsubscribed me from the Try Guys. WTF YT?!?

No idea when exactly, but I just suddenly stopped seeing them. It was around a time when new videos hadn't seemed to be posted quite as much (at least it seemed like it anyway) and after a few days I figured they were just busy doing something- new great content, be it videos, podcasts, books, more tour stuff, whatever- and that they were just coming a bit slower than norm.

As I was subscribed (as far as I knew anyway =/ ) I expected to just get updates, and didn't give it much more thought (guess that was dumb smh.) After a bit, I didn't even think about checking manually, but apparently I should have.

Anyway thanks to this videos D&D subject being somewhat related to other stuff I watch it was thrown in my recommendations. A pleasant surprise, but damn YT, I missed so much. I guess at least now I have a ton of backlogged content to pour over 🙄

Otherwise, glad the guys are still around and generating enjoyment for this ever darkening world; thanks for your videos in general, and especially for this awesome D&D video. Would absolutely love to see more; having them play super obscure, weird games would be great too imo. 👍

snippet.textDisplay: this is eye opening. hehe for me, growing up in Malaysia, I heard of dungeons and dragons but I never knew that the game is like this. I knew that it was kind of like a board game, but it's not really the kind of games we play here, we do play board games like snakes and ladders, monopoly, ludo,  chess, chinese checkers, checkers, scrabble...but this game is also a dice board game and is very intriguing, I wish I had this when I was younger. I knew of this game in movies, tv shows, but never knew exactly how to play and what is is like before watching this video. With that said, love ya Try Guys!
